                                                                        <div id="elementor-tab-content-2204" class="elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix" data-tab="4" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="elementor-tab-title-2204">
                                                                            <p>Ringless Voicemail is treated as a “Call” under TCPA laws and regulations. According to the laws, it&#8217;s important to have written consent from recipients before calling. Currently, it lies in a grey area with TCPA and other authorities. However, ringless voicemail providers don’t consider the RVM as a call and state that it is a non–intrusive marketing platform which does not create any disturbance.</p>
                                                                            <p> It is legal to use RVM under TCPA rules and regulations if you avoid contacting individual listed in the National DNC.</p>
                                                                        </div>
